76561198054024600,Not Recommended,321870,20796537,"Posted: 27 January, 2016",all,Bananarumpus,"I wish that I could leave a more neutral feedback for this game. It's pretty good, but also pretty bad.The style of the game caught my attention. It has a pretty unique look to it. I'm a fan of the contrasting silhouettes of the characters against the backgrounds with the occasional pop of color. Looks aren't everything, so moving on.Another reviewer mentioned that this game is like a 2D Silent Hill, and that's basically what sold me on this game. I do agree, that there are some similarities, but once I made it to chapter 3, I began to feel like playing this was more of a chore than any fun. Don't get me wrong, there are some parts of this game that are down right interesting and fun to play.. but there are other areas (the lock picking puzzle................) that are just frustrating as hell.Basically,-Some puzzles are interesting, others are a pain in the♥♥♥♥♥and I didn't find them clever or satisfying to solve.-The controls are clunky. I use the default Shift key to run and I'll randomly stop running and just casually stroll. I've tried key-binding my run to my mouse, but it was the same problem.-The ""combat"" has some unique bits to it. Once you get the hang of the pattern each monster follows, you'll be fine though. So it's really not that difficult.-At several moments throughout my play though, I ran around in circles looking for the trigger to move on in the story only to find out that I wasn't facing the right direction or in the exact position to speak with someone or pick something up.-The aesthetic and soundtrack are both fantastic.Right now, I'm taking a break from this game. I just finished the lock-picking nonsense, so I saved, and I'm done for awhile. I might come back and keep going because just prior to that, I thought that the art therapy room was a really neat touch. I'm just finding that one annoyance is enough to kill my morale for playing this game. I would like to know what's going on with Jacob though, so I'll likely keep going unless something reeeeeeeeeally ticks me off. That's when I'll just watch the ending on Youtube or something. ♥♥♥♥ it."
